# Capturing & Annotating a Snip

Learn how to capture a screenshot and annotate it with Snips.dev.

---

### 1. Open the Snip Tool
- Click the Snips.dev extension icon in your browser
- Select **Capture Region** or **Full Page**

---

### 2. Annotate Your Screenshot
Use the toolbar to:
- Draw arrows or highlight text
- Add comments, blur sensitive info
- Apply color filters or crop the image

![Annotation UI](https://placehold.co/600x300?text=Annotation+Tools)

---

### 3. Save & Share
- Add a title, tags, and description
- Choose visibility: Public, Private, or Team
- Click **Upload Snip**

You're all set! Others can now comment, react, or fork your snip.

